John<br>
No need to take sides, just write what's on your mind. I appreciate your words of friendship and wisdom. You can rest assured I did not take them lightly, I understand. Thank you<br><br>
I do believe, however, had I been sitting in the Congress, during the Prez state of the union address and when he mentioned in his speech, &quot;If we want America to lead, we must set a good example,&quot; while Republicans only shouted their agreement, I would have stood up and walked out.  <br><br>
Paul, <br>
Boy when you write you strike for the belly of the dragon, kiss it on its forehead and then cut out its guts, we'll need to keep you out of Wal-Mart, but then again I would want you at my side, in the heat of battle. <br><br>
You remind me of this Marine who had left his unopened coke on top of an amtrack. During the battle we all saw the coke just sitting there, bullets, tracers, grenades exploding all around the track. And then, this Jarhead runs up grabs the coke and jumps back behind the dike where we were. <br>
 <br>
Just that little bit of, dedication, craziness, was enough for us to become more determined in our desire to prevail that day. <br><br>
Perhaps that can of coke symbolized America, sitting there on top of that amtract, that we didn't want the enemy to hit or shoot at, I don't know, I do know we all felt good at what he had done. <br><br>
John,<br>
getting back to Iraq, I believe Saddam knows very well what he is doing, I wouldnt put it pass him to lined military targeted areas with children. He is doing the same as Ho Chi Minh did during Vietnam. He wants to divide this nation. And Clinton will do it, with limited public support, he will strike. <br><br>
But I fear that by the President's own words to the American people of the possiblities of suffering causalities from accidents and unforseen circumstances as we prepare to and strike out at Iraq, will come back and strike a fatal blow to his presidency. By his own words he has spoken how I believe God will bring down this president.<br><br>
Cook<br><br>

